entry.title: media/video/VEA: Add DropFrameMetadata to BitstreamBufferMetadata
entry.content:
BitstreamBufferMetadta for a dropped frame doesn't have any info about

codec metadata (e.g. spatial index). This is because no valid value

can be filled to some of the codec metadata (e.g. temporal index) and

we would like to avoid a client from wrongly referencing invalid

values.

However, this makes a client difficult to handle a dropped frame in

SVC encoding because a client cannot know a spatial layer index.



This CL introduces DropFrameMetadata. It is set if and only if a

frame is dropped. The metadata has useful info for the dropped frame.

It has spatial index so far.

entry.title: TaskAttribution: Change type hierarchy to allocate less
entry.content:
This CL changes the Task Attribution types so that we can propagate the

same ScriptWrappableTaskState object instead of creating a new one

every time:

- TaskAttributionInfo becomes a pure virtual interface. This class

will eventually hold the SoftNavigationContext.



- TaskAttributionInfoImpl is added as the sole implementation of

TaskAttributionInfo. Separating the impl allows us to access

core/ and inherit directly from ScriptWrappableTaskState, which in

turn allows us to propagate that object directly.



- WebSchedulingTaskState is added as a subclass of

ScriptWrappableTaskState that holds subtask-propagatable state

(TaskAttributionInfo) and continuation-only web-scheduling state

(priority and abort sources).



- Finally, we directly propagate TaskAttributionInfo objects when

there is no web scheduling task state to propagate



Note: this deviates a bit from the type hierarchy described in the

design doc because we no longer need to expose both continuation-only

and subtask propagatable task state now that CPED is more robust

(crrev.com/c/5316657).



Design doc:

https://docs.google.com/document/d/1hZ1FdFtHoPk7h9mwTPJSlF83T7YnTpmfa0CEQbPn8Ks/edit?usp=sharing

entry.title: WebApps: Store whole sync proto to prevent losing new fields
entry.content:
Currently we convert a WebAppSpecifics sync proto into several fields

which are stored on the WebApp struct (or its WebAppSpecifics struct) in

memory. When writing to disk or sync we convert back into a

WebAppSpecifics proto. This conversion causes data loss of new fields

and new field values when handled by older clients.



This CL stores the sync proto directly on the WebApp struct so lossy

conversions aren't done and the data is maintained. An exception is that

we still actively convert absent UserDisplayMode values into set values,

and proto2 (which we are using) represents unknown enum values as

absent. A follow-up CL could change this to lazily set UserDisplayMode

values instead, in order to preserve new enum values.

entry.title: Add Bluetooth LE Audio support
entry.content:
This CL adds the necessary change to allow chromium to recognize and

connect to Bluetooth LE Audio enabled devices.



Android supports 2 BT connections at once. Since LE Audio is a

separate Bluetooth profile than "classic" BT, this CL originally

tracked each profile separately, in case of multiple devices being

connected at once. However, `getAvailableCommunicationDevices()` only

returns the last connected BT device, regardless of whether it is a

"classic" or "LE" device. This means that we cannot target a specific

device when 2 are connected, and it's simpler to conflate the status of

both profiles.

entry.title: [OOPIF PDF] Use the PDF embedder host for saving URL using PDF UI
entry.content:
Use the PDF embedder host instead of the PDF content host when saving

the URL using the PDF UI.



PDFDocumentHelper is initialized when the PDF content host binds the

PDF service, so PDFDocumentHelper::render_frame_host() should reference

the PDF content host. OOPIF PDF was incorrectly using that host to

save the URL, when it should have been using the PDF embedder host.



This went undetected, since

PdfDownloadTestSplitCacheEnabled.SaveSubframePdfFromPdfUI_IsolationInfo

was incorrectly using the PDF embedder host to create the

PDFDocumentHelper.



Using the PDF content host instead of the embedder host would result in

incorrect network::ResourceRequest::TrustedParams.

entry.title: Remove unused VR UI code
entry.content:
Cleans up some more VR UI code that's unused. A few notable changes:



LinearLayout::layout_length_ was only set in UTs so was 0 in production.

This means that some of it's overrides were not necessary, and were

removed.



Extensive cleanup was done to UiElement to remove methods that were

unused (i.e. not called outside UTs), including several virtual methods

with no overrides. Virtual methods with no overrides and no impl in the

base class were deleted, whereas virtual methods with no overrides but

an impl were marked as non-virtual. This included removing a bunch of

logic for HitTests, Clipping and EventHandling that were tested in UTs

but not used outside of them as well as a few setters who were either

always set to the default value or the set value was never actually

read.



Also removed ControllerModel and TextureCopyRenderer which were

fully unused, as well as cleaning up the UiElementType enum.



Finally, removed some values from ColorScheme that weren't referenced

anywhere. A future cleanup can look at taking ColorScheme away from

entry.title: Remove child content selector from StylableSelect UA rules
entry.content:
This patch removes the :-internal-select-author-datalist and

:-internal-select-author-button pseudoclasses. Based on the standards

discussions, it seems like we will always render the potentially

problematic select UA rules instead of trying to detect whether the new

content model is used or if the computed value of appearance is the new

entry.title: Reduce the volume of readability requests.
entry.content:
We found that we send a lot of urls that are never used because of redirects. This has impact both on the traffic volume as well as the prediction quality for the speculative readability checks. on*LoadStarted and onTabSelected are called for the redirect urls so we shouldn't use these methods anymore to trigger readability checks. Instead, a combo of onUrlUpdated and onTabShown covers most cases that onTabSelected and on*LoadStarted cover. The missing cases (like triggering readability checks after opening a new tab) will be triggered by extra checks from the entrypoints (both of which can be dynamically refreshed now). In other words, there should be no regression in entrypoint visibility.

entry.content:

widget is closed. However, the recursive call in

running and cause the crash. This CL fix the crash by using ViewTracker

and checking for out of memory pointers.



Also change `view_` to be a ViewTracker for better memory management.
